Package jetbrains.mps.nodeEditor.highlighter

Class EditorCheckerWrapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • jetbrains.mps.nodeEditor.highlighter.EditorCheckerWrapper
  • public class EditorCheckerWrapper
extends Object
    Wraps an EditorChecker to provide for synchronous stopping.

    Implementations of EditorChecker are periodically called asynchronously from a background thread. When a plugin is unloaded, its checkers are removed from the highlighter and after removal their classes are unloaded. To do this correctly, it must be possible to stop a checker and make sure it is not invoked after a certain point in time.

    • Method Detail

      • stop

        public void stop()
        Marks this instance as stopped. After this method returns, other instance methods will not call the delegate but will either do nothing or return a default value. The only exception is getEditorMessageOwner() which will continue to work.

        Note that some checkers may have their own dispose() method. The responsibility of that method is different. stop() marks the checker as no longer being used by the highlighter, while the checker's dispose() method would detach listeners or close other resources used by the checker.
